article.headline: Wecker posts record 40th double-double
article.linkText: Wecker, Kansas St. devour Central Connecticut
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. (AP) -- Kendra Wecker had 24 points and 10
rebounds for her Kansas State-record 40th career double-double,
leading the No. 22 Wildcats a 77-23 victory over Central
Connecticut State on Sunday.

Wecker went 10-of-17 from the floor, including 4-of-5 from
3-point range. Nicole Ohlde held the previous record of 39 career
double-doubles.

Kansas State (9-2) won its fifth straight and improved to 67-1
when scoring at least 70 points. The loss was the seventh straight
for Central Connecticut State (1-8).

Laurie Koehn added 15 points on 5-of-9 shooting from 3-point
range.

The Wildcats led 29-16 at the half before outscoring the Blue
Devils 48-7 in the final 20 minutes. Kansas State finished the game
on a 31-1 run.

Twiggy McIntyre finished with 14 points for Kansas State.

Brittney Dixon led Central Connecticut State with eight.
